>> OH, THAT'S RIGHT.

08:55.135 --> 08:57.103
SO, WE HAD BEEN SEEING A QUITE

08:57.103 --> 09:00.073
ROBUST JOB GROWTH BEFORE MARCH,

09:00.073 --> 09:01.674
THE PREVIOUS 12 MONTHS.

09:01.674 --> 09:02.809
WE'D SEEN THE STRONGEST JOB

09:02.809 --> 09:04.577
CREATION ON A MONTHLY AVERAGE

09:04.577 --> 09:06.513
SINCE THE 1990s.

09:06.513 --> 09:08.081
SO, CERTAINLY, THAT WAS QUITE

09:08.081 --> 09:09.182
STRONG.

09:09.182 --> 09:10.116
WE HAD A STEP-BACK IN MARCH.

09:10.116 --> 09:10.884
THAT COULD BE FOR A NUMBER OF

09:10.884 --> 09:12.485
REASONS, INCLUDING, YOU KNOW, A

09:12.485 --> 09:15.622
STRONGER DOLLAR REDUCING

09:15.622 --> 09:17.056
EXPORTS.

