AND THERE'S AN ECONOMIC SLOWDOWN

09:18.925 --> 09:21.361
IN ASIA AND PARTS OF EUROPE, AND

09:21.361 --> 09:22.495
THAT MIGHT JUST BE CAUSING

09:22.495 --> 09:23.763
BUSINESSES TO BE A LITTLE BIT

09:23.763 --> 09:24.531
CAUTIOUS.

09:24.531 --> 09:26.466
THE TREND FOR JOBS IS STILL UP.

09:26.466 --> 09:27.934
WE EXPECT TO SEE WAGES

09:27.934 --> 09:30.136
ACCELERATE IF WE CONTINUE TO BE

09:30.136 --> 09:30.904
ADDING JOBS AT THE PACE WE HAD

09:30.904 --> 09:32.105
BEEN BEFORE LAST MONTH.

09:32.105 --> 09:33.540
>> Sreenivasan: ALL RIGHT, ERIC

09:33.540 --> 09:34.374
MORATH OF THE "WALL STREET

09:34.374 --> 09:35.141
JOURNAL" JOINING US FROM

09:35.141 --> 09:36.242
WASHINGTON, THANKS SO MUCH.

09:36.242 --> 09:37.677
>> SURE, ANY TIME.

